The first setup of vim for Windows.

1.Dowonload gvimxx.exe from "www.vim.org"

2.Clone "dotfiles" repository from git.

3.Clone "neobundle.vim" repository from git.
  git clone git://github.com/Shougo/neobundle.vim c:\Users\user-name\.vim\bundle\neobundle.vim
  or
  git clone https://github.com/Shougo/neobundle.vim c:\Users\user-name\.vim\bundle\neobundle.vim

4.Clone "vimproc.vim" and build vimproc_win32.dll
  >cd C:\Users\ユーザー名\.vim\bundle
  >git clone https://github.com/Shougo/vimproc.vim.git vimproc
  >cd vimproc
  >make -f make_mingw32.mak

5.Execute "symbolic.bat" to make symboliclink.


6.Make gitconfig
.gitconfig
[user]
  name = mukaiizawa
  email = mukaiizawa@yahoo.co.jp
[http]
  proxy = http://xxx


Cautions!
The path of git is letting it pass. 


